About 2,750 persons from Katsina State are expected to perform this year’s hajj exercise. Daily Trust reports that about 4800 seats were allocated to the state by the National Hajj Commission (NAHCOM) Addressing journalists weekend, the Executive Secretary of the State PilgrimsWelfare Board, Abu Rimi, said the board was working round the clock to ensure a smooth exercise. According to him, the biometric capture of all pilgrims was being finalised as mandated by Saudi authorities adding that “vaccination and sensitization of pilgrims are also ongoing”. In a related development, a statement by the spokesman of the board, Badaru Karofi, said the board had completed the distribution of hand luggage and pilgrims uniforms. “We are only awaiting schedules and Basic Travel Allowances for the commencement of airlift from the state,” he said.